BFN 

  [Text] Pale/Augsburg (DPA) -- Serbian military have 
temporarily put a German television team of the SAT-1 private 
station under house arrest in the Bosnian town of Pale. On 
Friday morning [22 April] the journalists, who had been detained 
the day before, were released again, the television station 
announced. The two reporters are supposed to leave the country 
today. 
  The television team had filmed scenes in the streets of 
Pale. 
Military officers stopped the filming and seized the technical 
equipment. The two journalists and their Serbian interpreter 
had to hand in their passports and their accreditations. They 
were prohibited from leaving the hotel, where they had been 
taken. 

